Chop the @British turkey steaks{2} into 1cm wide strips and pop in a #mixing bowl{}. In a #small bowl{}, combine the @hoisin sauce{25%g}, @soy sauce{12.5%ml}, @cornflour{10%g} and @water{200%ml} along with a pinch of @salt{} and @black pepper{}. Mix together thoroughly, then add half of the marinade mixture to the turkey. Coat the turkey in the marinade and leave to one side.

Boil the @water{300%ml} in a #large saucepan{}. Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and cover with a #lid{}. Cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~{10%minutes}.

> The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, halve, then remove the core from the @bell pepper{1}(halved and cored) and chop into 1cm pieces (or as small as you can).

> If you don't like chilli then don't bother! Finely slice the red into rounds. Alternatively, if you don't like so much heat, halve the chilli lengthways and deseed before slicing.

Finely slice the @red chilli{1/2}(finely sliced) into rounds.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the turkey and stir-fry until brown on all sides, ~{4-5%minutes}. Next, add the pepper and cook, stirring, until just soft, ~{4-5%minutes}. Now add the @sugar snap peas{150%g} and stir-fry for ~{1-2%minutes}. Finally, add the remaining marinade and cook, stirring, for ~{2-3%minutes}.

> If the mixture is a little dry, add a couple of tbsp of water to loosen it up.

Time to build your own meal! If you want to keep it simple for the kids, serve as it is: fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and serve in #bowls{} with the stir-fried turkey and veggies.

For a little bit more excitement, stir the @sesame seeds{15} through the turkey and veggies until they cling to everything. Sprinkle the @coconut powder{25%g} into the rice and gently stir it through (add as much as you like to taste). Serve the coconut rice in bowls with the hoisin turkey stir fry on top, scattered with some @?red chilli{1/2} if you like heat! Enjoy!